def: Pelts or skins, collectively; skins with the fur on them; furs.
The act of drinking or tippling together. [R.]The fashion of compotation. Sir W. Scott.
Of or pertaining to funerals; funereal.
A storm, strong wind, or gale coming from the southeast.
The forward part of the hold of a ship.
Furnished with qualities; endowed. [Obs.] "He was wellqualitied." Chapman.
A manufacturer of tin vessels; a dealer in tinware.
Olefiant gas, or ethylene; hence, by extension, any one of theseries of unsaturated hydrocarbons of which ethylene is a type. SeeEthylene.
Not lovely; not amiable; possessing qualities that excitedislike; disagreeable; displeasing; unpleasant.-- Un*love"li*ness, n.
A countryman; a rustic; especially, one of the lowest class oftillers of the soil in European countries.
A cart so constructed that the body can be easily tipped, inorder to dump the load.
